<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 2nd graf to restore time element.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By SHARON HERBAUGH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>GOINDWAL, India (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Prime Minister <PERSON> Rajiv </PERSON> <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON>, protected by a bulletproof vest and shield, appealed for help in his government's fight against Sikh terrorism on his first visit to the embattled <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> since 1985. <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON> placed the foundation stone for a new paper mill in this small village amid tight security on his one-day trip Wednesday to the northern state, where Sikh extremists are fighting for an independent homeland. The government hopes the $ 170 million mill will help pump new life into a state shattered by six years of guerrilla and terrorist attacks. Sikh radicals have killed more than 1,950 people in <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> this year, nearly double the toll for 1987. The prime minister was accompanied by more than 6,000 paramilitary troops, mostly armed with steel-tipped bamboo sticks, and stood at the podium behind a bulletproof shield. `` The anti-nationals want to break democracy in <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>, but we must give our lives to maintain it,'' <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON> said, wearing a bulletproof vest as he addressed the crowd of 15,000 factory workers, students and teachers. `` We have no fight with the Sikhs, only the terrorists. We are fighting strongly, and we are getting results,'' the prime minister said, speaking in <LOCATION> Hindi </LOCATION>. <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> is the only Indian state with a Sikh majority. Nationwide, members of the Sikh faith comprise just 2 percent of <LOCATION> India </LOCATION>'s 800 million people, but they form 60 percent of <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION>'s 18 million people. <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> has been one of the biggest crises for the <LOCATION> Gandhi </LOCATION> government, which fears the separatist movement could become a full-scale civil war and fan insurgencies by other restless minorities. `` We maintain respect for all religions,'' <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON> told the crowd. <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON>'s mother, Prime Minister <PERSON> Indira </PERSON> <PERSON> Gandhi </PERSON>, was assassinated by two of her Sikh bodyguards in October 1984, four months after she ordered an army raid on the <ORGANIZATION> Golden </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Temple </ORGANIZATION> in the <LOCATION> Punjab </LOCATION> city of <LOCATION> Amritsar </LOCATION>, where Sikh militants were holed up. More than 2,000 people, mostly Sikhs, died in the raid on <LOCATION> Sikhdom </LOCATION>'s holiest shrine.
