<HEAD>Nine Injured as Engine Breaks Off, Enters Commuter Plane</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAVID BAUDER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ALBANY, N.Y. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A piece of the engine of a <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION> commuter airplane broke off, punctured one of the craft's windows and entered the passenger cabin, injuring as many as nine people, authorities said. A witness described a `` loud bang'' about 10 minutes before the four-engine DeHavilland-7 turboprop was dueto land Wednesday at <LOCATION> Albany </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> with 13 passengers and three crew members aboard. The pilot of Flight 878, which originated at <ORGANIZATION> John </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> F. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kennedy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airport </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>, said nothing to the passengers and the 50-seat craft appeared to land normally, said one passenger, A.K. <PERSON> Gupta </PERSON> said. There were conflicting reports of injuries early today. <PERSON> Todd </PERSON> <PERSON> Saterlee </PERSON>, manager of passenger services for <ORGANIZATION> Pan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Am </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Express </ORGANIZATION>, said there were seven people hurt. However, a spokesman for the <ORGANIZATION> Albany </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Medical </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hospital </ORGANIZATION> said nine people were admitted there. All but one of those injured were treated and released, said the spokesman, <PERSON> Richard </PERSON> <PERSON> Puff </PERSON>. The injuries consisted of smoke inhalation, cuts from glass fragments or, in one case, a minor burn, said Puff. The only passenger admitted was <PERSON> Steven </PERSON> <PERSON> Roecker </PERSON>, 33, of <PERSON> Rexford </PERSON>. He suffered eye and facial injuries and was in fair condition, <PERSON> Puff </PERSON> said. His wife, <PERSON> D