<HEAD>Tearful Victim Testifies In Gang Rape Trial</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Leads with 7 grafs to UPDATE with woman's testimony, edit,
picking up 7th graf pvs, `The woman ....' Note contents.</NOTE>
<BYLINE>By JOEL WILLIAMS</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>SAN DIEGO, Texas (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A tearful woman, clutching a stuffed animal, broke down on the witness stand today after testifying that she was raped and sodomized by a group of men. `` I was screaming and telling him to stop. ... He was holding my legs. I was trying to push him off,'' the 19-year-old woman said of defendant <PERSON> Orlando </PERSON> <PERSON> Garza </PERSON>, 23, the first to be tried of the 10 men indicted in the case. She said <PERSON> Garza </PERSON> was laughing as he raped her on the hood of a car, and that other men nearby joined in and also sexually assaulted her. After she had testified for about one hour, the court recessed when the woman, in tears, said she was about to faint. On Wednesday, the doctor who examined the woman said she was scratched and bruised, including internal bruises, when she arrived at a hospital for treatment. `` She told me she had been sexually assaulted by as many as 20 to 23 men,'' said Dr. <PERSON> Vilma </PERSON> <PERSON> Garcia </PERSON>, who examined her at <ORGANIZATION> Humana </ORGANIZATION> Hospital-Corpus Christi on March 27. The woman said `` that they were her neighbors,'' <PERSON> Garcia </PERSON> testified Wednesday in the sexual assault trial. Assistant District Attorney <PERSON> Rodolfo </PERSON> <PERSON> Gutierrez </PERSON> said he expected the woman to continue her testimony later today. The woman, who was a resident of <LOCATION> San </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Diego </LOCATION> at the time, told authorities she was kidnapped and sexually assaulted by the men over a period of several hours on the night of March 26-27. All 10 have pleaded innocent to charges including kidnapping, aggravated kidnapping and sexual assault. `` This was not a kidnapping,'' defense attorney <PERSON> Albert </PERSON> <PERSON> Pena </PERSON> said in an interview Wednesday. `` She voluntarily went.'' <PERSON> Jose </PERSON> <PERSON> Carlos </PERSON> <PERSON> Briones </PERSON> testified Wednesday that the woman scratched her attackers, cried out for help and fainted while she was being raped on the hood of a car outside town. <PERSON> Briones </PERSON>, 29, said the woman cried: `` Help me, please help me.'' `` She was moaning and groaning. She had tears in her eyes,'' <PERSON> Briones </PERSON> said in Spanish through an interpreter. `` I was the only one who told them to leave her alone,'' said <PERSON> Briones </PERSON>, who also faces a sexual assault charge in the case. Prosecutors have promised to recommend probation for <PERSON> Briones </PERSON> in exchange for his testimony. <PERSON> Briones </PERSON> says he was impotent at the time of the attack from drinking too much beer. When <PERSON> Pena </PERSON> asked him if the woman was making sounds of pleasure, <PERSON> Briones </PERSON> answered: `` It was nothing about being happy.'' He said <PERSON> Garza </PERSON> held the woman's wrists during part of the attack. `` He -LRB- <PERSON> Garza </PERSON> -RRB- told me to hold her because she was scratching him,'' <PERSON> Briones </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Briones </PERSON> said he saw several of the other defendants assaulting the woman. Sexual assault is punishable by two to 20 years in prison and-or a fine of up to $ 10,000. The woman, her husband and two children have moved to an undisclosed location in another city because of reported harassment since she accused the 10 men.
