<HEAD>More Than 100 Die In Flood</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: UPDATES thruout with 106 deaths.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>KATMANDU, Nepal (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A flash flood ripped through a mountain village and killed more than 100 people, including four policemen, authorities said Thursday. Home Ministry officials confirmed the deaths of 106 people and said the toll may still be higher because several visitors spent the night in the area Tuesday. The officials said at least 58 people lost their lives in <LOCATION> Darwang </LOCATION> village, 125 miles west of <LOCATION> Katmandu </LOCATION>, and 48 others died in nearby <LOCATION> Niskot </LOCATION>. Only four bodies have been recovered. Rescuers were searching for others. The flood began Tuesday night when a boulder broke loose from a landslide that dammed the <LOCATION> Myagdi </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION> and created a huge lake.
