n rite, <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON> spoke about <PERSON> DelGado </PERSON>, saying he believed the attacker did n't `` have the slightest idea what he was doing.'' `` For it to have happened here is a special sacrilege and tragedy,'' <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON> said, adding that <PERSON> St. </PERSON> <PERSON> Patrick </PERSON>'s was a `` magnet for Catholics everywhere.'' `` While the cathedral has been desecrated, while this magnificent temple of almighty God, famous throughout the world, has been violated, we must not forget that two men were killed here last night,'' <PERSON> O'Connor </PERSON> told several hundred people attending the first Mass of the day. `` It is for their souls I will be offering this Mass, as well as for the purification of the cathedral.''
