ANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> that it has begun preliminary negotiations with third parties about issuing preferred stock to them, a step that would make the company harder to take over. <PERSON> Shamrock </PERSON>, which is owned by the family of <PERSON> Roy </PERSON> <PERSON> E. </PERSON> <PERSON> Disney </PERSON>, nephew of the late animator <ORGANIZATION> Walt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION>, says that if its bid succeeds it would drop <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION>'s fledgling venture into 35mm film, sell most of the company's undeveloped real estate, narrow the company's manufacturing facilities and simplify <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION>'s research and development activities to focus on the company's core businesses The offer hinged on the invalidation of <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION>'s recent issuance of 9.7 million shares to a new employee stock ownership plan, a move <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> made early in its attempt to block <PERSON> Shamrock </PERSON>.
