<FIRST>r f AM-GMAdPlan     09-22 0460</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-GM Ad Plan,0477</SECOND>
<HEAD>West Virginia Scuttles GM Plan To Pass On Ad Costs To Buyers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By T.J. SIMONEAUX</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>CHARLESTON, W. Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has agreed to revise an advertising plan that state authorities say would boost car prices while illegally forcing dealers to participate, according to Attorney General <PERSON> Charlie </PERSON> <PERSON> Brown </PERSON>. Separately, a group of <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> auto dealers has sued to block a similar advertising plan in their state. <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Chevrolet </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> division planned to increase the amount its dealer franchises pay for their cars by 1 percent _ an average of $ 40 to $ 50 a car _ to finance a dealers association that would run the automaker's national advertising campaigns. The company offered dealers who joined the association a 25 percent discount on the surcharge, but told those who did not join that they would not receive the discount, <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said Wednesday in announcing the settlement. Under the plan, the dealers would pass on the surcharge to car buyers. Chevrolet planned to begin the program with its September shipments and tacked the 1 percent charge on to its dealers' bills for this month. `` A lot of dealers complained about it,'' <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said he learned about the Chevrolet plan in August. <PERSON> Steve </PERSON> <PERSON> Herndon </PERSON>, solicitor general for the attorney general's office, investigated the plan, then informed <LOCATION> Chevrolet </LOCATION> that it violated <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION> law. Under the law, autmobile dealers can not be required to participate in a dealers association. `` This type of deceptive business practice is a violation of fair trade competition, and the consumer is the ultimate victim,'' <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said. `` Obviously, if <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> dealers have to compete with other <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> dealers -LRB- in advertising -RRB-, it means better prices for consumers,'' <PERSON> Herndon </PERSON> said. The attorney general's office and Chevrolet last week negotiated a settlement under which dealers will participate in the ad plan only if they want, and then pay the discounted fee. Those who do n't participate will be paid an amount equivalent to the 25 percent discount Dealers did not pay the September charge, <PERSON> Herndon </PERSON> said. At least 27 other states have auto dealer laws similar to <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Virginia </LOCATION>'s, the attorney general said. Other automakers _ including <ORGANIZATION> Ford </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> _ have tried similar tactics, <PERSON> Brown </PERSON> said. In <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION>, the <ORGANIZATION> Ohio </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Automobile </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dealers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> and three <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> dealerships sued <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> and its <ORGANIZATION> GMC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Truck </ORGANIZATION> and Chevrolet divisions in <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> District </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Columbus </LOCATION>, alleging a similar advertising program in <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> violates state law prohibiting mandatory participation in a dealers association. They plaintiffs want the court to stop the program and award them any damages allowed under state law, plus double the amount <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> has collected under the program. The Sept. 8 suit has not been scheduled for trial. <ORGANIZATION> GM </ORGANIZATION> has not filed a response.
