<SECOND>BC-EEC-Colgate,0093</SECOND>
<HEAD>Colgate-Palmolive Prepares For 1992</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Consumer-products giant <ORGANIZATION> Colgate-Palmolive </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said Thursday that it was consolidating its European operations in prepartion for the single market being targeted by the European Ecoomic Community for 1992. The <ORGANIZATION> EEC </ORGANIZATION> hopes to eliminate all barriers to movement of capital, goods, services and people by that date. <ORGANIZATION> Colgate-Palmolive </ORGANIZATION>, based in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, has several subsidiaries throughout <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> with about 6,000 employees. Its European sales total about $ 1.8 billion. Other <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> companies are expected to consolidate their European operations.
</TEXT>
