<HEAD>PNC Financial, Delaware Banks to Merge</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> PNC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> said Thursday they plan to merge operations in an agreement valued at $ 230 million. <ORGANIZATION> PNC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Pittsburgh </LOCATION> is the nation's 12th largest bank holding company with assets of $ 36.8 billion. It has about 475 banking offices in <LOCATION> Pennsylvania </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Kentucky </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Indiana </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Ohio </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Wilmington </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Del. </LOCATION>, is the holding company for the <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION>, the state's second largest bank, and has assets of $ 1.8 billion. The <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> has 33 branch offices in the state. The <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Delaware </ORGANIZATION> will retain its name, existing management and its headquarters while operating as a group within <ORGANIZATION> PNC </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>, the companies said. `` The merger will expand <ORGANIZATION> PNC </ORGANIZATION>'s presence in <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jersey </LOCATION> to strategic points in <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Delmarva </LOCATION> <LO