<HEAD>With BC-Longest Bid</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Here's a chronological look at some of the key events in the <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>'s hostile takeover attempt of <ORGANIZATION> Irving </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>: Sept. 25, 1987 _ <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> makes an unsolicited $ 1.4 billion cash-stock bid for <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>. Oct. 9 _ <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s board rejects the $ 1.4 billion bid, activates the company's `` poison pill'' anti-takeover defense. Nov. 20 _ <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> lowers its offer to $ 1.2 billion, citing the Oct. 19 stock market crash. Dec. 15 _ <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s board rejects <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>'s $ 1.2 billion bid. Jan. 25, 1988 _ <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> lowers its bid to $ 1.08 billion, citing <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s decision to increase its fourth-quarter loan-loss reserve. Feb. 16 _ <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s board rejects <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>'s $ 1.08 billion bid. Feb. 25 _ <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>'s takeover proposal gets approval from the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Banking </ORGANIZATION> boards. March 15, 28 _ Irving amends its poison pill. April 14 _ <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION>'s shareholders give their blessing to an Irving merger. April 18 _ <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Italiana </ORGANIZATION> enters the picture, offering $ 65 a share for 51 percent of <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>. <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> announces a major resturcturing. April 20 _ <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> offers $ 75 a share for 45 percent of <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>. May 2 _ <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> raises its proposed stake to 51 percent at the same price. May 6 _ <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s shareholders re-elect <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s directors, although <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> later challenges the proxy results in court. May 23 _ <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> raises its bid for 51 percent of Irving to $ 80 a share. The value of the offer is upped to $ 84 a share a few weeks later. June 15 _ <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> conditionally offers to raise the stock portion of its bid, valuing the offer at $ 1.4 billion. <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> later rejects the proposal. The previous offer, valued at about $ 1.2 billion under current market conditions, stands. July 6 _ <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> State </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Supreme </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> strikes down a provision of <PERSON> Irving </PERSON>'s poison pill. <PERSON> Irving </PERSON> vows to appeal. Aug. 19 _ The <ORGANIZATION> Fed </ORGANIZATION> rules the <LOCATION> Italian </LOCATION> government agency that owns most of <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> has to supply financial information in the Irving bid. Aug. 29 _ <ORGANIZATION> Banca </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commerciale </ORGANIZATION> withdraws its bid. Sept. 7 _ Fed grants <ORGANIZATION> Bank </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> another 90-day extension to complete the Irving merger, pending appeal of the poison pill case.
