<HEAD>Hunts `Upbeat' Despite Filings</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By JAY JORDEN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DALLAS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 One of three Hunts facing a $ 134 million federal court judgment did not follow the lead of his brothers in filing personal bankruptcy petitions because he did not have as much potential exposure in the claim, a spokesman said Thursday. Heirs to one of the world's greatest fortunes, <PERSON> Nelson </PERSON> <PERSON> Bunker </PERSON> and <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> Herbert </PERSON> <PERSON> Hunt </PERSON>, two of the multimillionaire <LOCATION> Dallas </LOCATION> brothers, filed bankruptcy Wednesday. But attorneys say the filings wo n't affect previous Chapter 11 bankruptcy proceedings involving the brothers' <ORGANIZATION> Placid </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Oil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION>, owned by their trust estates. Jurors in a <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> federal court decided Aug. 20 the two Hunts, their brother <PERSON> Lamar </PERSON> and three other defendants must pay damages for conspiring in the late 1970s to corner the world's silver market, and ruining the investments of <ORGANIZATION> Minpeco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> SA </ORGANIZATION>, the Peruvian government's mineral marketing company `` They -LRB- the brothers -RRB- are very upbeat. There is not anybody hanging their head over this,'' said a spokesman, <PERSON> Tom </PERSON> <PERSON> Whitaker </PERSON>, executive vice president for the <ORGANIZATION> Hunt </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Energy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp </ORGANIZATION>. He said <PERSON> Lamar </PERSON> <PERSON> Hunt </PERSON> did not file a personal bankruptcy petition because he does not have the exposure of the other two brothers. But the spokesman did not rule out the possibility of a later filing. `` It was his -LRB- <PERSON> Lamar </PERSON>'s -RRB- option not to file,'' said <PERSON> Whitaker </PERSON>. `` He does not have the involvement in the potential silver litigation that <PERSON> Bunker </PERSON> and <PERSON> Herbert </PERSON> have. He does hav