 </PERSON> <PERSON> Simon </PERSON> of <PERSON> Simon </PERSON>, <PERSON> Anisman </PERSON>, <PERSON> Doby </PERSON>, <ORGANIZATION> Wilson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Skillern </PERSON>. Confirmation hearings for Placid, which begin Monday before <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bankruptcy Judge <PERSON> Harold </PERSON> <PERSON> Abramson </PERSON>, should be completed by the end of next week, he said. `` I do n't think it -LRB- the personal bankruptcy petitions -RRB- have any effect on Placid,'' he said. `` I believe Placid's reorganization will proceed and it will be a reorganized company. `` By the end of next week, we should have confirmation in which we satisfy that the plan is feasible, that the company can pay for everything the -LRB- <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> -RRB- Bankruptcy Code provides and, regarding deferred obligations, whether there is a reasonable basis for the business plan so that creditors who vote for the plan have a reasonable chance of getting their money,'' said <PERSON> Simon </PERSON>. <PERSON> Whitaker </PERSON> said the two Hunts' personal bankruptcy petitions did not list value of their assets but that, `` as the case proceeds through the bankruptcy court, those values will be established.'' However, brief summaries of their assets detailed 13,649 Byzantine coins and 44 pieces of a Roman and Greek bronze collection for <PERSON> Herbert </PERSON> <PERSON> Hunt </PERSON>. <PERSON> Bunker </PERSON> <PERSON> Hunt </PERSON>'s petition noted ancient coins and `` various art objects and bronze statues.'' Bunker Hunt listed oil and gas properties in 40 counties nationwide, three gas plants, 14 ranches, 1,390 acres of raw land, a condo in <LOCATION> Kauai </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Hawaii </LOCATION>, five cars and a host of other assets, the <ORGANIZATION> Dallas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Morning </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> News </ORGANIZATION> reported. <PERSON> Herbert </PERSO