<HEAD>Late Rally Called Key Reversal For Grain Futures</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By DAVID DISHNEAU</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 A late rally that pushed grain and soybean futures prices higher Thursday on the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Trade </ORGANIZATION> could mark a key reversal in the market's recent downward trend, analysts said. On other markets, gold struggled back to $ 400 an ounce; copper surged; frozen pork bellies rose sharply while livestock futures were mixed; energy futures were mostly higher; and stock-index futures retreated. Soybeans for November delivery, which had traded as high as $ 9.03 -LCB- a bushel just one week earlier, swung in a 28-cent range Thursday, plunging to $ 8.15 but settling near the day's high at $ 8.42, 4 -LCB- cents above Wednesday's final price. Corn and wheat futures also finished moderately higher but were less volatile due to the supportive influence of new export business, analysts said. `` The -LRB- soybean -RRB- market liquidated early until there just was n't any selling left below $ 8.20 Then the strength in the wheat and corn really supported the bean complex,'' said <PERSON> Pat </PERSON> <PERSON> O'Connell </PERSON>, a grain analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Refco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>, a <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> futures brokerage. `` I think the market told us today that it's in good shape,'' he said. <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Mao </PERSON>, grain specialist with <ORGANIZATION> Shearson </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lehman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Hutton </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, said the drop to $ 8.15 `` appears now in hindsight to have been the end of the liquidation,'' he said. `` Today could be a bullish key reversal,'' agreed <PERSON> Mario </PERSON> <PERSON> Balletto </PERSON>, soybean market analyst with <ORGANIZATION> Merrill </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Lynch </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Capital </ORGAN